               <head>Grant; Gazeley; 1315</head>
               <msContents>
                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <p>
                        <placeName key="place_111660">Gazeley</placeName>. <origDate when="1315">1315</origDate>. 
                        Grant from <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> le <surname>Warde</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_111664">Kentford (Kenteforde)</placeName></persName>, to <persName>
                           <forename>Walter</forename> 
                           <surname>Priour</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_111667">Needham Street (Nedham)</placeName></persName>, <persName nymRef="Priour">
                           <forename>Petronilla</forename> his wife</persName>, and <persName nymRef="Priour">
                           <forename>John</forename> their son</persName>, for a sum of money, of a rood of arable land in the parish of Gaysle, in the field called <placeName type="minor">Walkerescrofthel</placeName>, between the lands of <persName>
                           <forename>Thomas</forename> 
                           <surname>Beyllard</surname>
                        </persName> and the aforesaid Walter.
                        Dated at <placeName role="date" key="place_111664">Kentford (Kenteforde)</placeName> on Sunday [27 July] before the feast of St Peter a[d] Vincula, 9 Edw. II [1315].
                        Witnesses: <persName>
                           <forename>Thomas</forename> 
                           <surname>Beylard</surname></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Howe</surname></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Pistore</surname>' of <placeName role="person" key="place_111664">Kentford (Kenteforde)</placeName></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>Robert</forename> of <surname>Hapetone</surname></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>Ralph</forename> 
                           <surname>(Townsend) 'ad capud ville'</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_111667">Needham Street (Nedham)</placeName></persName>, and others.
                        Endorsed: Joh. Ward.
                     </p>
                  </msItem>
